Description:
    Generates a form builder that creates a form from an activity in the WebCRM. To create an
    example use the "--cms_path" parameter. In the WebCRM you can create a new activity type, where
    you can add your form attribute, choose their input type and set required fields.

Example:
    `rails generate cms:component:form_buider`
    `rails generate cms:component:form_buider --cms_path=/website/en`

    CMS: obj_class FormBuilder
           attribute headline (string)
           attribute content (html)
           attribute show_in_navigation (enum)
           attribute sort_key (string)
           attribute crm_activity_type (string)

    CRM: Activity type 'contact-form' with attributes 'email' and 'message'